 media group was founded in  as danoo and got financial backing from kleiner perkins caufield  byers dag ventures national cinemedia and tennenbaum capital partners in july  danoo acquired ideacast in august  the company renamed itself rmg networks and appointed garry mcguire to take over as ceo from aileen lee in may  rmg sold its digital signage network targeting cafes small restaurants and juice bars for an undisclosed sum to san franciscobased brite media in april  the company acquired symon communications a digital signage company founded in  for  million and moved its headquarters from san francisco to the dallas metropolitan area where symon communications was located the company went public via a reverse merger with scg financial acquisition corp in april  external linksedit rmg networks rmg networks investor relations referencesedit  httpwwwrmgnetworkscomnewsrmgnetworksnamesrobertmichelsonceo  danoo acquires ideacast to put ads in gyms and airplanes venturebeat july    danoo  ideacast relaunch as reach media group dailydooh august    danoo lands new chief executive for digital outofhome ads venturebeat july    rmg acquires symon communications mediapost april    digital signage biz rmg networks goes public at  a share in reverse merger venturebeat april    rmg goes public with reverse merger san francisco business times april   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlermgnetworksoldid categories signage companiescompanies based in texas establishments in texas navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprin